{{c|dos2unix}} is a tool to convert text files from DOS line endings (carriage return + line feed) to Unix line endings (line feed). It is also capable of conversion between UTF-16 to UTF-8. Invoking the {{c|unix2dos}} command can be used to convert ''from'' Unix ''to'' DOS. This tool comes in handy when sharing files between Windows and Linux machines.

